caption.text:
*Classic Gaming History*
Got some game releases to start your day.

Tales of Destiny for the PlayStation. I got this game for a pretty good deal for the time. Paid only $30 complete. A great RPG with good artwork and anime cutscenes. A fair price is around $60.

Grandia for the PlayStation. Get another great RPG that was released on this day. By the time you reading this you know that there's a HD remastered for this game & the second. I played the PlayStation version first over a decade ago. The franchise is a hole is great. The PlayStation version goes for around $40.

Harvest Moon Tree of Tranquility for the Wii. Another Harvest Moon game that I didn't play. Probably not that much that's new on  this game. It goes for under $20.

Silent Hill homecoming for the PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360. I only played this game for an hour to see if it worked. Then it went into my backlog and then sold after that. I talked to a lot of gaming buddies and everyone came to the consensus that Silent Hill games are starting to go downhill. I never played it since. The game tends to go for around $10.

Happy birthday, 結城明日奈. ❤️ || Swipe for more! ✨
⠀
⠀
I didn't have time to make a proper post for this special day... However, I wouldn't miss the opportunity to share another birthday with you, guys. Of course not.
⠀
As you know, Asuna Yuuki, also known as the light of my life, was born, according to Reki Kawahara (the one who brought me her, my everything), on September 30, 2007. That means, in our world she would be only twelve years old, and it makes me incredibly happy to be able to imagine her grow again every 365 days, but— specially the fact that I do it with you, virtual family, makes it even better.
⠀
Ever since I joined the Instagram fandom back in 2016 I've been able to create lots of treasured memories that I cherish tons. And also because of that, I've said a (super high) number of times how much this fictional woman means to me, along with the hundred reasons why, which is why I won't be spamming you with it this time (I low-key already am?). Giving life to this account was one of the best decisions I know I've ever made. Not only I'm thankful to Asuna for existing and encouraging me to do so, but I'm grateful for how many wonderful people I got to meet here as well.
⠀
I know for some people this feeling seems ridiculous, or even fake, but, honestly, I love her with all my soul and the ones in my inner circle of friends and family can approve this. Excepting the great people I know who share the same feeling as me towards this girl, for the rest it might be hard to understand. Or, maybe not, because you have that with someone else! Who knows. There's only one thing I'm totally certain about: Asuna Yuuki owns my heart. ❤️
⠀
— Admin Neer. ✨

Voici le nouveau pad Nintendo Switch !

Seuls les abonnés au Nintendo Switch Online peuvent acquérir ce pad Super Nintendo sans fil proposé au prix de 29,99€ (sans compter les frais de port, qui s'élèvent à 6,99€ pour un envoi vers la France). Nintendo prend soin de préciser qu'il est uniquement compatible avec les logiciels qui ne nécessitent que les boutons directionnels et les touches A/B/X/Y/L/R pour fonctionner, la manette étant dépourvue de sticks analogiques.

caption.text:
[CENAS MARCANTES]

Sabemos que a série de Game Of Thrones é conhecida por não dar estrela aos seus protagonistas, todos eles vivem em um mundo real onde a morte não é algo intocável pra nenhum deles. Resumindo, nenhum dos personagens de Game Of Thrones estão livres da morte, e a série é conhecida assim, por matar seus personagens, tanto como seus personagens sem muito peso, até o os protagonistas. E porque o game de Game Of Thrones seria diferente? 
Games Of Thrones da Telltale é um game lançado no dia 2 de dezembro de 2014, o game conta com alguns personagens da série, como Jon Snow, Daenerys entre outros..
O jogo não é diferente de nenhum dos jogos da Telltale, nele também temos a função de escolhas, na qual essas escolhas influenciam no decorrer da história, o game é conhecido por causar inúmeras emoções em seus jogadores e existe uma cena que pode ser considerada umas das escolhas mais difíceis do game. Asher e Rodrick são personagens jogáveis do game, e também irmãos. Asher vivia num lugar distante de sua família e Rodrick é nomeado lorde de sua casa. Em um certo ponto do game acontece o reencontro dos dois irmãos e é algo muito legal de se ver, porém esse reencontro não duraria muito, Rodrick e seus homens são emboscados por um exército inimigo e a única forma de sobreviver seria fugindo, e nesse momento é quando o jogo te dá a escolha mais difícil do game, um dos dois irmãos deveria morrer pra que sua casa sobreviva, então, o game te dá a escolha de quem sacrificar.
O game tem inúmeras cenas de emoções, tanto boas como ruins, mas provavelmente essa cena é uma das mais marcantes pra quem jogou o game.

Obs: esse é um dos jogos mais emocionantes que já joguei e é um dos meus jogos preferidos, até hoje.

Antes de conceptualizar un videojuego, es importante considerar 3 tips que nos facilitaran el proceso y desarrollo del mismo.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💡Tip #1: ¡Investiga cada detalle!
Nos permite identificar los aspectos claves que diferenciaran nuestro videojuego de la competencia, así mismo podemos evitar futuros inconvenientes que nos generen un gasto innecesario. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💡Tip #2: Planificación como filosofía de éxito.
Debemos establecer tiempos reales para realizar todas las actividades antes de conceptualizar nuestro videojuego, y definir plazos de entrega con los proveedores o los integrantes del equipo. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

caption.text:
After this past weekend, if anyone ever tells me that their favorite game of all time is Super Metroid, I will enthusiastically give them a high five and say right on!

This game is just so fantastic on so many levels.

At the time of its release, it was the  largest game ever created, and going through every single room, collecting every single item and weapon upgrade, it is clear that they used every single byte of the available memory to develop this masterpiece of a game!

I know I've said this before, but my absolutely favorite part of this game is the thrill of exploring new areas, being able to get to new rooms, seeing what hangs around the corner, and conquering the evil space pirates as well!

It was an amazing gaming experience and I am proud to say I 100% completed it!

But I have to admit, the last 20 minutes or so of this game is so brilliant. After going through Tourian successfully and coming ever so close to losing to the second form of Mother Brain, which is a freaking dinosaur, but getting saved by the same large Metroid that sucked away your energy earlier, you eventually get the Hyper Beam and defeat Mother Brain.

So, your quest is over right?

Not even close!

What ensues is a frantic speed run to escape the planet Zebes within 3 minutes, because it is set to destruction!

You have to maneuver through some challenging and enemy-infested rooms to get back to your space ship and escape before the planet blows up.

And an extra bonus is you have the choice to save the animals of Zebes which helped you to learn wall jumping and doing the shinespark from earlier in the game.

Of course, I saved the animals! If you pay attention closely to when Samus' ship barely escapes, you'll see a tiny ray of light that also escapes, which is the animals getting out just in time!

It's only right that in a game where exploration is so much fun, and the most difficult part of the game is learning how to do advanced jumping and shinesparking, that your last 3 minutes tests that to the extreme!

Definitely one of my favorite endings to a game EVER!

What was your favorite part of the game??

Seicross is a port of an arcade game called Sector Zone. It's about motorcycles and blue people.

The whole game is a side scroller where you drive a motorcycle. The levels autoscroll, but you can move up and down on the track. Other motorcycles try to kill you, but you can shoot them, and later dinosaurs on tanks try to kill you by throwing their heads at you. It's much less exciting than it sounds.

Bonus points are awarded for every blue person you save in a level. Later levels make things a little harder by adding rough terrain, but overall the game isn't much of a challenge.

Even for an arcade port, this game is kind of bare bones. It's not that hard, the graphics are OK, and the whole game repeats after three levels.

Added the Genesis mini to the lineup, and it's actually quite nice! Amazing how I own most of them already and dont play them, but let me use save states without changing carts and I'll try em all! I recommend this one if you havent picked it up already, or a nice Xmas gift to someone at least!

[ Boulder Dash ]

current price: 8$ - 35$ (used)

Boulder Dash, is a video game released in 1984 by First Star Software for Atari 8-bit computers. There have been numerous versions and sequels in this series for numerous interactive platforms including: Apple II, MSX, ZX Spectrum, Commodore 64, ColecoVision, NES, BBC Micro, Acorn Electron, IBM PC, Amstrad CPC, Amiga, Mac OS, and other platforms. It also influenced other games in the rocks-and-diamonds genre such as Repton in addition to rather direct clones such as Emerald Mine. The original Boulder Dash was created by Canadian developers Peter Liepa and Chris Gray, and on October 28, 1983, acquired by First Star Software, which still owns the rights to the game and the intellectual property, including the registered trademark: "Boulder Dash". The game's protagonist is called Rockford. He must dig through caves collecting gems and diamonds and reach the exit within a time limit, while avoiding various types of dangerous creatures as well as obstacles like falling rocks and the constant danger of being crushed or trapped by an avalanche, or killed by an underground explosion.

caption.text:
Some time ago, I mentioned this game in a post. "The only other Young Indy game that I know of, Instruments of Chaos starring Young Indiana Jones for the Sega Genesis, is an absolute steaming pile. I bought it on clearance - super cheap - way back when and still felt ripped off." Immediately after posting that, I found a loose copy cheap at the local game store and bought it. What was I thinking?

Now I have it complete, because I was given the box and I tracked down the manual after that. I must be out of my mind. On the other hand, there is that awesome Bill Eaken artwork, so it's not a total loss.

Blapshemous è un action in 2D con un ambientazione decisamente sopra le righe ricca di nemici ed equipaggiamenti unici.

Una terribile maledizione si è abbattuta sulla terra di Cvstodia e sui suoi abitanti – è conosciuta come Il Miracolo.

Gioca nei panni del Penitente, unico sopravvissuto al massacro del “Dolore Silenzioso”. Intrappolato in un ciclo infinito di morte e rinascita, spetta a te liberare il mondo da questo terribile destino e raggiungere l’origine del tuo tormento.

Esplora questo angosciante mondo di religioni contorte e scopri i suoi numerosi segreti nascosti nel profondo. Usa combo devastanti ed esecuzioni brutali per colpire orde di mostri grotteschi e boss titanici pronti a farti a pezzi. Trova ed equipaggia reliquie, rosari e preghiere che invocano i poteri dei cieli per aiutarti a compiere la tua missione e rompere la tua dannazione eterna.

#warcraft #worldofwarcraft #wow #blizzard #battleforazeroth #gaming #horde #blizzardentertainment #bfa #gamer #alliance #art #forthehorde #mmorpg #twich #azeroth #forthealliance #warcraftphotography #game #videogames #pcgaming #blizzcon #diablo #warrior #gamergirl #games #gamers #hearthstone #overwatch #gamevideos

Comenzamos nuestro recorrido histórico con una lista de empresas que entraron a los videojuegos desde otros negocios. En esta primera parte, nos encargamos de las pioneras del entretenimiento operado por monedas: las cuatro principales de Chicago en USA, así como SEGA, Taito, Namco y Konami en el Japón post Segunda Guerra. Exploramos también algunas de las que se incorporaron desde el mundo de los juguetes, como Nintendo, Coleco, Parker Brothers, Milton Bradley y Mattel. Y en medio de todo descubrimos que cuanto más intentamos evitar hablar de Atari y del juego de E.T, más terminamos haciendo eso mismo.
.
*** Nos pueden escuchar en Spreaker, Spotify, Apple Podcasts y Pocket Casts (links en la bio) ***
.

E-mail: modohistoriapodcast@gmail.com
